{"id":29,"date":"2019-11-21T00:45:37","date_gmt":"2019-11-21T00:45:37","guid":{"rendered":"http:\/\/calvaryopcny.org\/?page_id=29"},"modified":"2026-04-19T14:24:33","modified_gmt":"2026-04-19T14:24:33","slug":"about","status":"publish","type":"page","link":"http:\/\/calvaryopcny.org\/about","title":{"rendered":"About"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<div style=\"background-color: #131e4c; text-align: center; color: #fff; width: 100vw;\n  margin-left: calc(-50vw + 50%); padding-top: 38px; padding-bottom: 38px;\">\n<h1>About Calvary Orthodox Presbyterian Church<\/h1>\n<\/div>\n\n\n\n<div style=\"padding-top:38px;\">\n<p> Calvary has proclaimed the good news of Jesus in the Capital District since 1938. We love Jesus, want to honor Jesus, and help each other grow closer to Jesus. Our heritage is Reformed, our tone is joyous, our worship is traditional and our disposition is welcoming.<\/p>\n<p>Our story really begins in Genesis 1-2: God created the heavens and the earth, and all they contain. He upholds and governs them in accordance with his eternal will. God is sovereign yet this does not diminish human responsibility. when after the fall of man (Genesis 3), God promised that in Redemptive History, one would come to crush the head of the serpent. God fulfilled that promise in the incarnation, ministry, death, burial, resurrection and ascension of our Lord Jesus Christ. He continues that story through the church today.<\/p>\n<p>Our particular story also has its roots in the Protestant Reformation. We are Reformed, and part of the Orthodox Presbyterian Church. We exist to joyfully worship the King of Kings, readily serve one another and eagerly tell others about the good news of Jesus Christ.<\/p>\n<\/div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"one-third first\">\n\t<img decoding=\"async\" src=\"http:\/\/calvaryopcny.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/02\/image-4.png\" alt=\"Calvary OPC NY\">\n<\/div>\t\n\n<div class=\"one-third\">\n\t<img decoding=\"async\" src=\"http:\/\/calvaryopcny.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/02\/image-5.png\" alt=\"Calvary OPC NY\">\n<\/div>\t\n\n<div class=\"one-third\">\n\t<img decoding=\"async\" src=\"http:\/\/calvaryopcny.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/02\/image-6.png\" alt=\"Calvary OPC NY\">\n<\/div>\n\n\n\n<p style=\"padding-top:36px;\">Pastor Thomas Trouwborst has served at Calvary since 2001, comes from NJ and used to work as a CPA.<\/p>\n\n<div class=\"one-third first\">\n\t<img decoding=\"async\" src=\"http:\/\/calvaryopcny.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/02\/IMG_0594.jpg\" alt=\"Calvary OPC NY\">\n<\/div>\t\n\n<div class=\"one-third\">\n\t<img decoding=\"async\" src=\"http:\/\/calvaryopcny.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/02\/IMG_5786-Edit-copy.jpg\" alt=\"Calvary OPC NY\">\n<\/div>\t\n\n<div class=\"one-third\">\n\t<img decoding=\"async\" src=\"http:\/\/calvaryopcny.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/02\/59061067296__B963E0DE-3DC1-4CE3-84C6-425B904C2180.jpg\" alt=\"Calvary OPC NY\">\n<\/div>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div style=\"background-color: #dbdbdb; text-align:center; color: #000; width: 100vw;\n  margin-left: calc(-50vw + 50%); padding-top: 38px; padding-bottom: 38px;\">\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><h1><span style=\"color: rgb(128, 101, 19);\">Church Is<\/span> <b>Important<\/b><\/h1><\/p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:left; margin-left:15%; margin-right:15%;\"> The church is God&#8217;s family, it is the household of God (Eph. 2:19-22). It is made up of a people who were once enemies of God but have been reconciled to Him.  It is the community of those who have been called out by God. The church is made up of &#8220;sinners&#8221; who have been called out of darkness. <\/p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:left; margin-left:15%; margin-right:15%;\">Jesus is the head of the church. In the church you hear the voice of Christ and see the gifts of the Spirit used. Jesus is committed to His church, He shed His blood for it and you can&#8217;t come to Jesus without coming to His people. To neglect the church is to neglect Jesus. Jesus gathers, protects, and preserves His church. God is actively calling the world to repentance and reconciling sinners to himself, and it is through the church that the mission of the Triune God is on display. Jesus builds up His people through it. Life is a battle, and the Christian life especially, is a supernatural battle and cannot be fought alone.<\/p>\n<\/div>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center\" style=\"padding-top:66px; margin-bottom:-36px;\">\u201cO Lord, our hearts are restless until they rest in you.\u201d<br><em>Saint Augustine<\/em><\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>About Calvary Orthodox Presbyterian Church Calvary has proclaimed the good news of Jesus in the Capital District since 1938. We love Jesus, want to honor Jesus, and help each other grow closer to Jesus. Our heritage is Reformed, our tone is joyous, our worship is traditional and our disposition is welcoming. Our story really begins [&hellip;]<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":0,"parent":0,"menu_order":0,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"closed","template":"","meta":{"_genesis_hide_title":true,"_genesis_hide_breadcrumbs":false,"_genesis_hide_singular_image":false,"_genesis_hide_footer_widgets":false,"_genesis_custom_body_class":"","_genesis_custom_post_class":"","_genesis_layout":"","footnotes":""},"_links":{"self":[{"href":"http:\/\/calvaryopcny.org\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/pages\/29"}],"collection":[{"href":"http:\/\/calvaryopcny.org\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/pages"}],"about":[{"href":"http:\/\/calvaryopcny.org\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/page"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"http:\/\/calvaryopcny.org\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/1"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"http:\/\/calvaryopcny.org\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/comments?post=29"}],"version-history":[{"count":80,"href":"http:\/\/calvaryopcny.org\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/pages\/29\/revisions"}],"predecessor-version":[{"id":1642,"href":"http:\/\/calvaryopcny.org\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/pages\/29\/revisions\/1642